data.name: lblListOfRules.Text
data.value: 1. Any “on” cell with fewer than two “on” neighbors “turns off,” as if by underpopulation. 2. Any “on” cell with two or three “on” neighbors lives on to the next generation. 3. Any “on” cell with more than three live neighbors “turns off,” as if by overpopulation. 4. Any “off” cell with exactly three “on” neighbors becomes a live cell, as if by reproduction
